Last month's tsunami could reduce  Indonesia's gross domestic product growth by 0.4 percent, but  Indonesia's improving financial situation means it is in good stead  to cope, the World Bank said Tuesday.
The US navy aircraft  carrier at the centre of American military aid efforts in  Indonesia's tsunami-hit Aceh is ending its mission and will leave  within 48 hours, US officials said Thursday.
Japan on Tuesday put its army, air force  and navy on standby to provide assistance to survivors of Asia's  tsunami disaster, with most of their work expected to be in  worst-hit Indonesia.
